    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1982-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1982-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <head>344. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d344fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Office of the Director of Central
                        Intelligence, Job 89B00224R: Committees, Task Forces, Boards, and Councils
                        Files, Box 11, Folder 406: Memos for the Record of Mtgs w/Sec and <gloss
                            target="#t_DepSec_1">DepSec</gloss> of State (Apr 81–Dec 85). Secret;
                        Eyes Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1982-06-15">June 15, 1982</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Breakfast meeting with Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HAM_1"
                            >Haig</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_ELS_1">Eagleburger</persName>,
                        DCI and DDCI on 15 June 1982</item>
                </list>
                <p>The following subjects were discussed:</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of issues unrelated to the situation in the South
                    Atlantic.]</p>
                <pb facs="0754" n="707" xml:id="pg_707"/>
                <p>—<hi rend="italic">Falklands.</hi> The DDCI reported on a <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss> cable indicating coup plotting is underway
                    against <persName corresp="#p_GLF_1">Galtieri</persName>.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d344fn2">Not found.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HAM_1">Haig</persName> believes <persName
                        corresp="#p_GLF_1">Galtieri</persName> will last no more than a week.
                    Meanwhile, there is general belief that <persName corresp="#p_TMH_1"
                        >Thatcher</persName> has been the one to push hard and that we need to
                    encourage her to be more moderate. <persName corresp="#p_ELS_1"
                        >Eagleburger</persName> said that the Salvadoran Ambassador and other South
                    American officials have relayed their belief that the U.S. will not be damaged
                    very much by the Falklands crisis and that the Latin American countries in
                    general will continue to look to the U.S. for leadership and economic support.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HAM_1">Haig</persName> did voice his concern about the
                    Salvadoran Army setback yesterday in their operation against the guerrillas.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of issues unrelated to the South Atlantic.]</p>
            </div>
